complete honesty from him...

01:17:27.395 --> 01:17:29.894
if I... if I'm asking any less
of myself?

01:17:29.895 --> 01:17:32.813
I mean, isn't that just
the height of hypocrisy?

01:17:32.814 --> 01:17:34.454
Could be.

01:17:36.276 --> 01:17:38.871
I don't hear much helping
going on over there.

01:17:39.571 --> 01:17:41.381
Sorry.

01:17:43.367 --> 01:17:45.132
Oh, God!

01:17:47.329 --> 01:17:50.971
- Does this hurt them?
- Not if you're gentle about it.

01:17:55.128 --> 01:17:56.813
I get it.

01:17:58.048 --> 01:17:59.984
Yeah, I get it.

01:18:00.092 --> 01:18:03.313
You're telling me to be honest...

01:18:03.804 --> 01:18:05.513
but to be gentle.

01:18:05.514 --> 01:18:08.656
I was telling you
to ease up on her teat.

01:18:08.892 --> 01:18:11.578
But I guess it works both ways.

01:18:11.645 --> 01:18:15.162
- That's very wise.
- I doubt that.

01:18:17.150 --> 01:18:20.462
That stuff you're talking about
isn't easy.

01:18:20.570 --> 01:18:23.948
It's like that book, Men Are From Mars,
and Women Are From Venus.

01:18:23.949 --> 01:18:25.616
You read that book?

01:18:25.617 --> 01:18:29.134
I read the cover.
That pretty much summed it up.

01:18:39.798 --> 01:18:41.517
Ringer!

01:18:41.675 --> 01:18:44.487
I give up, Clay. You're too good.

01:19:00.318 --> 01:19:03.209
Well, hello there. I'm glad you came.

01:19:16.960 --> 01:19:18.794
Thank you, Ray!

01:19:18.795 --> 01:19:23.313
Keep your dancing shoes on
'cause now we're gonna kick it.

01:19:23.425 --> 01:19:25.520
- Come on, you're dancing.
- Really?

01:19:44.112 --> 01:19:45.780
- I wanna tell you something.
- I know,

01:19:45.781 --> 01:19:48.968
- I'm very light on my feet.
- No. Well, yes.

01:19:49.034 --> 01:19:51.220
But something else.

01:19:53.038 --> 01:19:57.101
I think we should go
to the official site together.

01:19:59.544 --> 01:20:01.354
You do?

01:20:02.547 --> 01:20:04.062
Yeah.

01:20:05.675 --> 01:20:08.511
- Well, that is so great.
- Good.

01:20:08.512 --> 01:20:11.608
- That is so great!
- I know. I know.

01:20:26.363 --> 01:20:28.628
And one other thing.

01:20:28.657 --> 01:20:30.126
Yeah?

01:20:30.450 --> 01:20:32.910
While we were separated,

01:20:32.911 --> 01:20:35.097
I slept with someone else.

01:20:36.915 --> 01:20:39.101
Switch partners!

01:20:59.271 --> 01:21:01.536
It just happened once.

01:21:01.982 --> 01:21:03.497
Once.

01:21:03.942 --> 01:21:06.068
Really, and it was just because
I was just...

01:21:06.069 --> 01:21:10.587
I was feeling, you know,
just hurt and rejected.

01:21:13.243 --> 01:21:15.202
- You're upset.
- No, no, no.

01:21:15.203 --> 01:21:18.038
I'm... What am I?
I'm a little bit surprised, I suppose.

01:21:18.039 --> 01:21:20.165
If you're gonna be mad, be mad,

01:21:20.166 --> 01:21:24.684
but please,
please don't stop talking to me.

01:21:24.838 --> 01:21:28.799
Yell, scream, I don't care.
You know, honestly, whatever you want.

01:21:28.800 --> 01:21:30.634
There is nothing to scream about.

01:21:30.635 --> 01:21:35.495
We were separated. You're an adult.
These things happen, so there it is.

01:21:36.516 --> 01:21:38.611
- Hey, Paul.
- Howdy.

01:21:46.109 --> 01:21:49.046
- Do you wanna ask me something?
- No.

01:22:02.042 --> 01:22:05.058
- Do you mind?
- No, no, no, no.

01:22:17.599 --> 01:22:19.391
Do you wanna talk?

01:22:19.392 --> 01:22:21.737
No, no. Unless you do.

01:22:22.187 --> 01:22:24.407
I always wanna talk.

01:22:25.482 --> 01:22:27.122
Go ahead.

01:22:31.279 --> 01:22:33.544
It's okay. Never mind.

01:22:59.307 --> 01:23:01.767
Hey, folks, come on down to Ray Rodeo.

01:23:01.768 --> 01:23:03.644
Calf ropin', bull ridin',

01:23:03.645 --> 01:23:06.787
pie-eating contest, great barbecue.

01:23:21.413 --> 01:23:23.303
Hey, excuse me.

01:23:23.415 --> 01:23:26.306
- How you doing?
- Howdy.

01:23:26.459 --> 01:23:29.294
I'm looking for two friends of mine,
Paul and Meryl.

01:23:29.295 --> 01:23:31.310
Oh, the Fosters.

01:23:32.090 --> 01:23:33.503
They're probably on their way
to the rodeo,

01:23:33.504 --> 01:23:35.843
but they're staying
with the Wheelers.

01:23:35.844 --> 01:23:38.220
Wheelers.
And where's that?

01:23:38.221 --> 01:23:41.765
Okay, so go down this road, and when
you see the broken fence, make a right.

01:23:41.766 --> 01:23:43.827
And then, when you come
to the second big rock...

01:23:56.823 --> 01:23:58.282
Morning.

01:23:58.283 --> 01:24:01.345
Better shake a leg if you want to eat.

01:24:02.579 --> 01:24:05.015
Do you know where Paul is?

01:24:06.291 --> 01:24:08.010
Thank you.

01:24:18.303 --> 01:24:20.898
Hey, can I ask you a question?

01:24:22.682 --> 01:24:25.142
Who do you think this is fooling?

01:24:25.143 --> 01:24:27.033
Isn't this...

01:24:27.562 --> 01:24:31.440
I mean, isn't this what screwed us up
in the first place, not talking?

01:24:31.441 --> 01:24:33.317
Is it? Is it really?
Sorry, it was stupid of me.

01:24:33.318 --> 01:24:36.528
I thought it was sleeping with other
people, but maybe you're right. Yes.

01:24:36.529 --> 01:24:38.155
All right, you know what? Never mind.

01:24:38.156 --> 01:24:39.823
All right. What would you like me to do?

01:24:39.824 --> 01:24:41.950
Would you like me to beg for information?
Then I will.

01:24:41.951 --> 01:24:44.467
- What was his name?
- Larry.

01:24:44.496 --> 01:24:46.887
Larry? Are you serious?

01:24:47.040 --> 01:24:48.165
Larry.

01:24:48.166 --> 01:24:50.209
You know, he's recently divorced.
He just asked me to dinner.

01:24:50.210 --> 01:24:51.835
It's fine, it's fine,
I think I got the picture.

01:24:51.836 --> 01:24:53.253
And then you probably had a few drinks,

01:24:53.254 --> 01:24:54.963
and you moaned
about your horrible husband,

01:24:54.964 --> 01:24:56.924
and then you went back to his apartment.
I got it. I got it.

01:24:56.925 --> 01:24:58.769
Well, no, no.

01:24:59.177 --> 01:25:01.693
Went back to our apartment.

01:25:01.805 --> 01:25:03.847
Right, we're selling the place.
Thanks so much for telling me.

01:25:03.848 --> 01:25:05.557
- Probably...
- You're upset.

01:25:05.558 --> 01:25:08.268
Look, we both made mistakes.

01:25:08.269 --> 01:25:12.356
I made a mistake, yours seems
just a little bit more like revenge.

01:25:12.357 --> 01:25:14.372
Are you serious?

01:25:15.693 --> 01:25:18.946
I mean, do you...
Do you not know me at all?

01:25:18.947 --> 01:25:21.865
You think that I would sleep with someone
for revenge. I would...

01:25:21.866 --> 01:25:23.659
I would sleep with someone to hurt you?

01:25:23.660 --> 01:25:25.619
Well, at this point,
I don't really know what I think of you.

01:25:25.620 --> 01:25:27.663
- Oh, my God. Screw you.
- Can I just say this?

01:25:27.664 --> 01:25:29.790
- Meryl. Can I just... Can I speak?
- No. You know what? No.

01:25:29.791 --> 01:25:32.209
- No. Not to me.
- Wait, Meryl, I'm not finished. Meryl!

01:25:32.210 --> 01:25:33.335
Ready to go?

01:25:33.336 --> 01:25:35.879
I think I'm gonna pass
on the rodeo. Sorry.

01:25:35.880 --> 01:25:38.066
Yeah. Sorry, me, too.

01:25:38.466 --> 01:25:40.652
I have a lot of packing to do.

01:25:40.885 --> 01:25:42.445
Sorry.

01:25:43.012 --> 01:25:44.777
Okay, then.

01:25:47.475 --> 01:25:49.115
Hold on.

01:25:52.230 --> 01:25:55.042
I know it's none of my business,

01:25:55.984 --> 01:25:58.110
but I've watched you two
over the past four days,

01:25:58.111 --> 01:26:03.096
laughing together
over your little inside New York jokes.

01:26:03.908 --> 01:26:06.299
I don't find them funny,

01:26:06.536 --> 01:26:11.206
but I think that you can always tell
a lot about a couple

01:26:11.207 --> 01:26:14.929
by the fact that they still
laugh together.

01:26:17.922 --> 01:26:20.438
Thanks, I appreciate that.

01:26:21.926 --> 01:26:25.318
And, I think... Yeah, I think he's funny.

01:26:25.680 --> 01:26:27.741
He makes me laugh.

01:26:28.433 --> 01:26:32.121
But if we're gonna stay together, then,

01:26:33.438 --> 01:26:37.941
you know, I guess
we have to scale back our expectations,

01:26:37.942 --> 01:26:40.527
and I won't expect everything from him,

01:26:40.528 --> 01:26:42.738
and he won't expect everything
from me and...

01:26:42.739 --> 01:26:46.131
You should expect everything
from each other!

01:26:46.409 --> 01:26:49.130
Marriage doesn't make any sense!

01:26:49.370 --> 01:26:50.704
You gotta stop thinking about it,

01:26:50.705 --> 01:26:54.427
and just get over
all the bullshit and make it work.

01:26:58.922 --> 01:27:01.965
Look, I figured if she said something,
I was gonna...

01:27:01.966 --> 01:27:05.028
Oh, God. Come on, honey, let's just go.

01:27:07.347 --> 01:27:10.739
We'll pick you up
and take you to the airport.

01:27:11.476 --> 01:27:13.320
I declare.

01:27:13.645 --> 01:27:15.687
I have not heard you talk that much in...

01:27:15.688 --> 01:27:18.830
Well, I had to offer my two bits' worth.

01:27:59.941 --> 01:28:01.410
Shit!

01:28:10.034 --> 01:28:11.952
- What was that?
- Oh, my God!

01:28:11.953 --> 01:28:14.079
- Oh, my God, it's him!
- We gotta call Clay and Emma.

01:28:14.080 --> 01:28:16.766
- No, no. The phone has a code.
- Christ!

01:28:27.051 --> 01:28:28.719
Excuse me.

01:28:28.720 --> 01:28:31.236
What are you, kidding?

01:28:42.066 --> 01:28:44.276
Oh, my God. I'm out of bullets.

01:28:44.277 --> 01:28:46.588
Something I never expected
to hear you say.

01:28:48.781 --> 01:28:51.627
We'll go out the back. Scuttle!

01:28:56.748 --> 01:28:58.217
Come on. Up, up.

01:28:59.625 --> 01:29:01.435
- Come on, come on, come on.
- I'm trying.

01:29:03.796 --> 01:29:05.297
Okay, Windy, go.

01:29:05.298 --> 01:29:07.063
Oh, my God.

01:29:25.860 --> 01:29:27.903
Okay, we gotta find Clay.

01:29:27.904 --> 01:29:30.169
Should be easy.
He's wearing a cowboy hat.

01:29:38.373 --> 01:29:40.082
Nice try, cowboy.

01:29:40.083 --> 01:29:44.180
Been a while since anybody rode this bull
to the eight-second mark.

01:29:44.879 --> 01:29:47.770
Looks like old Buster won another round.

01:29:48.591 --> 01:29:51.482
Dumped him
like a blushing bride at the altar.

01:29:53.471 --> 01:29:55.972
Doc Simmons and the boys
have a dangerous job,

01:29:55.973 --> 01:29:58.364
protecting these bull-riding cowboys.

01:29:59.310 --> 01:30:01.228
That's a lot of bull,

01:30:01.229 --> 01:30:03.188
and that ain't no bull.

01:30:03.189 --> 01:30:05.204
Hey, that's Clay.

01:30:05.525 --> 01:30:07.651
He's in the box. Go, go, go.

01:30:07.652 --> 01:30:11.215
Folks, let's have a big hand
for our bull-fighting clowns.

01:30:18.788 --> 01:30:21.998
Folks, we got a little treat for you
today before our next bull.

01:30:21.999 --> 01:30:25.482
Here's hometown trick-rider Carly Ames.

01:30:36.931 --> 01:30:38.696
Oh, my God.

01:30:39.976 --> 01:30:42.162
Just sit. Just sit.

01:30:52.071 --> 01:30:53.711
Scuttle.

01:31:14.510 --> 01:31:18.107
Nice riding, Carly. Thank you.

01:31:18.514 --> 01:31:21.451
Folks, let's give her a big hand.

01:31:22.393 --> 01:31:24.561
Next up is Tom willet.

01:31:24.562 --> 01:31:27.783
Tom's riding
the aptly-named bull, Killer.

01:31:29.525 --> 01:31:33.528
The last 3 cowboys to get on this bull
got dumped right out of the gate.

01:31:33.529 --> 01:31:37.012
Let's see if Tom can break that streak.

01:31:44.999 --> 01:31:47.139
There he goes.

01:31:51.672 --> 01:31:53.381
Go get him, boys.

01:31:53.382 --> 01:31:55.443
Let's go, come on!

01:31:57.053 --> 01:32:00.263
Old Killer's living up to his name today.

01:32:00.264 --> 01:32:02.529
What's happening? I can't see.

01:32:08.814 --> 01:32:10.624
Oh, my God.

01:32:12.944 --> 01:32:16.086
- What's that noise?
- Oh, God. Just run!

01:32:16.113 --> 01:32:19.676
- Just run!
- I'm running! I don't have a choice!

01:32:23.454 --> 01:32:26.540
- Meryl, you all right?
- No.

01:32:26.541 --> 01:32:29.251
- I really think I hurt my leg.
- Oh, God.

01:32:29.252 --> 01:32:31.938
I don't think I can walk.

01:32:32.213 --> 01:32:34.798
Oh, my God.
We're never gonna get away from him.

01:32:34.799 --> 01:32:36.860
What? Where is he?

01:32:38.427 --> 01:32:39.970
Oh, God.

01:32:39.971 --> 01:32:42.806
Alright. Wait there. Wait there.
I'll be back in a minute.

01:32:42.807 --> 01:32:46.226
Wait, what, what? Wait,
what're you doing? Where're you going?

01:32:46.227 --> 01:32:50.245
- Please, don't leave me. Paul!
- Just keep your head down.

01:33:00.032 --> 01:33:01.157
Bollocks!

01:33:01.158 --> 01:33:04.925
Hey. I got plenty of room on my wall
for another head.

01:33:05.204 --> 01:33:08.415
Drop it, son.
Step back away from my lawyer.

01:33:08.416 --> 01:33:10.917
I should just point out that
even if you kill me,

01:33:10.918 --> 01:33:13.461
you now have two more witnesses
who will testify against you.

01:33:13.462 --> 01:33:15.422
- Three.
- Four.

01:33:15.423 --> 01:33:17.215
- Five.
- Five.

01:33:17.216 --> 01:33:19.527
- You're six, Kell.
- Six.

01:33:34.483 --> 01:33:35.918
Oh, my God.

01:33:43.784 --> 01:33:45.535
You all right?

01:33:45.536 --> 01:33:48.538
Are you crazy?
You could have been killed.

01:33:48.539 --> 01:33:51.374
I am just very touched
that that would've bothered you.

01:33:51.375 --> 01:33:53.835
Well, of course it would have.

01:33:53.836 --> 01:33:56.101
Oh, God, I had this...

01:33:56.339 --> 01:34:01.009
This horrible moment where I pictured
what life would be like without you.

01:34:01.010 --> 01:34:02.844
That's exactly what I had.

01:34:02.845 --> 01:34:05.347
When you were lying here,
sprawled in the dust,

01:34:05.348 --> 01:34:07.265
all I wanted to do was protect you.

01:34:07.266 --> 01:34:09.657
I lost all physical fear.

01:34:09.810 --> 01:34:12.354
It's coming back now, though.
What in God's name was I thinking?

01:34:12.355 --> 01:34:14.731
I know exactly what you were thinking.

01:34:14.732 --> 01:34:17.901
You were thinking
that we're meant to be together,

01:34:17.902 --> 01:34:20.070
because look what you did.

01:34:20.071 --> 01:34:22.489
You risked your life for me.

01:34:22.490 --> 01:34:24.366
That's so nice.

01:34:24.367 --> 01:34:26.451
- No.
- Sorry.

01:34:26.452 --> 01:34:29.138
No, no. I am sorry.

01:34:29.413 --> 01:34:33.852
I am so sorry
for nearly curing an incurable romantic.

01:34:34.001 --> 01:34:37.087
I want you to expect everything from me.

01:34:37.088 --> 01:34:41.151
You're not gonna get it,
but I promise to try and give it.

01:34:41.425 --> 01:34:43.486
I love you, Meryl.

01:34:43.719 --> 01:34:46.846
If you are in fact Meryl.
I can't really see, I'm sorry.

01:34:46.847 --> 01:34:48.987
I'm Meryl, trust me.

01:34:50.768 --> 01:34:53.614
'Cause I trust you all over again.

01:35:12.707 --> 01:35:14.541
Watch your head, please.

01:35:14.542 --> 01:35:18.336
Goodbye, Lucy. I hope
I get to hear you on the radio soon.

01:35:18.337 --> 01:35:20.853
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

01:35:20.965 --> 01:35:22.799
- Earl.
- Lucy.

01:35:22.800 --> 01:35:25.885
- Eat some meat.
- Eat some meat. Okay.

01:35:25.886 --> 01:35:27.846
- Okay, good. Good.
- Take care.

01:35:27.847 --> 01:35:29.931
Earl, I think we've become good friends.

01:35:29.932 --> 01:35:32.976
- Think what you want.
- Or not. Whatever.

01:35:32.977 --> 01:35:37.120
- So...
- I don't know what to say, except

01:35:37.690 --> 01:35:42.038
we are really, truly sorry about...

01:35:42.820 --> 01:35:43.987
- About everything.
- Yeah.

01:35:43.988 --> 01:35:45.155
Don't be.

01:35:45.156 --> 01:35:48.700
The Feds are so happy with us,
they're letting Clay keep his job.

01:35:48.701 --> 01:35:50.702
Is that right? That's great news.

01:35:50.703 --> 01:35:53.549
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

01:35:53.581 --> 01:35:55.665
Mr. and Mrs. Morgan, we're ready for you.

01:35:55.666 --> 01:35:58.887
Okay. Well, I suppose this is it.

01:35:59.128 --> 01:36:00.920
If we're ever attacked by a bear
in Central Park,

01:36:00.921 --> 01:36:02.714
we will be the only ones
who know what to do.

01:36:02.715 --> 01:36:06.482
You just take good care
of my favorite cousin, okay?

01:36:06.761 --> 01:36:09.137
- Emma.
- Goodbye, Paul.

01:36:09.138 --> 01:36:12.974
Really, thank you for everything,
and remember my wood-chopping tips.

01:36:12.975 --> 01:36:16.186
- I'll never forget your wood-chopping.
- It's mainly wrist, it's less arm.

01:36:16.187 --> 01:36:20.284
Clay, I'm gonna hug you.
You won't like it, but I'm gonna hug you.

01:36:21.525 --> 01:36:23.818
Thank you.
And listen, if you're ever in New York...

01:36:23.819 --> 01:36:26.631
Something has gone terribly wrong.

01:36:28.574 --> 01:36:31.090
Okay. Well, let's go home.

01:36:31.619 --> 01:36:33.338
- All right.
- Come on.

01:36:35.539 --> 01:36:37.600
How's your foot?

01:36:37.833 --> 01:36:40.710
Sheriff, your life just got
a whole lot simpler.

01:36:40.711 --> 01:36:42.647
So did yours, babe.

01:37:16.080 --> 01:37:19.207
Isn't it amazing
that she slept the whole flight?

01:37:19.208 --> 01:37:20.416
Is that amazing?

01:37:20.417 --> 01:37:21.668
- Are they not meant to do that?
- Yes.

01:37:21.669 --> 01:37:23.980
- Is she faulty?
- Faulty?

01:37:25.089 --> 01:37:27.298
No, she's perfect.

01:37:27.299 --> 01:37:29.008
Perfect, but nameless.

01:37:29.009 --> 01:37:32.262
Well, perhaps we'll finally come up
with a name on the road home.

01:37:32.263 --> 01:37:35.014
She could be Midtown Tunnel Morgan.

01:37:35.015 --> 01:37:36.599
59th Street Bridge Morgan.

01:37:36.600 --> 01:37:38.893
Hey, there's Adam and Jackie. Hi.

01:37:38.894 --> 01:37:40.228
Get their bags.

01:37:40.229 --> 01:37:42.856
- Should I get a cart?
- You are the cart. Go.

01:37:42.857 --> 01:37:44.326
Hey.

01:37:45.025 --> 01:37:47.871
- Thank you, honey.
- You're my girl.

01:37:48.195 --> 01:37:49.664
Go.

01:37:55.119 --> 01:37:56.536
Hurry, get that.
Get the phone.

01:37:56.537 --> 01:37:59.053
Yes, yes, yes, yes, yes.

01:38:01.000 --> 01:38:02.560
Hello?

01:38:02.710 --> 01:38:05.103
Oh, hello, Adam,
I've missed you.

01:38:05.204 --> 01:38:07.007
Uh, no, no, I'm taking
the day off tomorrow,

01:38:07.008 --> 01:38:09.257
so you do not need to come in.

01:38:09.258 --> 01:38:11.148
Yes, I'm sure.

01:38:12.303 --> 01:38:15.597
Well, in that case, have fun moving
Jackie's mother's furniture.

01:38:15.598 --> 01:38:18.535
I see many happy years ahead of you.

01:38:19.727 --> 01:38:21.446
Okay, bye.

01:38:22.313 --> 01:38:23.605
You know what I wish?

01:38:23.606 --> 01:38:27.400
I wish that as an older, wiser couple,

01:38:27.401 --> 01:38:30.820
we could give them some advice
like Clay and Emma gave us.

01:38:30.821 --> 01:38:33.948
Or we could just send them
to Ray for the weekend.

01:38:33.949 --> 01:38:35.384
Rae.

01:38:37.202 --> 01:38:42.187
We'll call her Rae. R-A-E. Rae.

01:38:42.791 --> 01:38:46.149
I quite like that. I quite like that.

01:38:47.296 --> 01:38:49.005
- Do you like that?
- Yes.

01:38:49.006 --> 01:38:51.382
No, no, not you. You.
What are your thoughts?

01:38:51.383 --> 01:38:54.479
- Rae?
- Rae Morgan.

01:38:55.346 --> 01:38:59.140
Hey, this is our new apartment, Rae.

01:38:59.141 --> 01:39:00.350
It's the one we had to get...

01:39:00.351 --> 01:39:01.721
because I didn't want to stay
in the old one...

01:39:01.722 --> 01:39:04.054
after Mummy slept there
with Larry.

01:39:04.355 --> 01:39:06.564
She doesn't need to hear this.

01:39:06.565 --> 01:39:08.024
Now, listen.

01:39:08.025 --> 01:39:10.860
Come here, little girl. It's got...

01:39:10.861 --> 01:39:12.797
Come on.

01:39:12.821 --> 01:39:16.133
...3,000 square feet.

01:39:16.200 --> 01:39:20.745
And a very spacious master bedroom.

01:39:20.746 --> 01:39:24.934
And come see this view.
Come look at this view, little lady.

01:39:26.794 --> 01:39:29.337
Right here, look at that.

01:39:29.338 --> 01:39:31.308
Can you believe?

01:39:31.548 --> 01:39:33.383
Is that something?

01:39:33.384 --> 01:39:35.445
It is, it is.

01:39:38.931 --> 01:39:41.617
That is quite a beautiful view.

01:39:43.769 --> 01:39:47.081
What? What?

01:39:47.731 --> 01:39:50.233
- How are you feeling, by the way?
- Good.

01:39:50.234 --> 01:39:53.080
- Everything all right?
- Very good.

01:39:53.320 --> 01:39:56.166
It'll be funny if this one
comes out Chinese, as well.

01:43:08.932 --> 01:43:11.726
Hi. You've reached Meryl Morgan.
I can't take your call right now,

01:43:11.727 --> 01:43:14.948
so leave a message
and have a great day. Thanks.

